 Marshall, Senior Coordinator, Touhill Performing Arts Center (St. Louis, MO)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"…I could fill the review page with the word, PERFECT, in a very large type!\"\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-David Nichols, Selection Committee Chair, Sarnia Concert Association (Sarnia, ON)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"...opening listeners\' minds to sounds and ideas they\'d never previously considered...\"\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Aidan Connolly, Executive Director, Irish Arts Center (New York, NY)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"... the band left the stage to thunderous applause.\"\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Geoff Shields, The Sioux Lookout Bulletin (Sioux Lookout, ON)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"It is rare for our audience members to immediately ask us to re-engage artists... <em>Sonic Escape</em> was one of those rarities. \"\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-John Ashton, President, Fairmont Chamber Music Society (Morgantown, WV)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"That was one of the best musical experiences of my life!  Can I give you a hug?\"\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Guy Jackson, Audience Member (Gravenhurst, ON)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"After many of your songs, I couldn\'t help but chuckle.  There was such life and joy.  The joy welled up and burst out!\"<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Dave Rockwood, Audience Member (Fairmo, WV)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"I\'ve been to performances all over Europe and America, and I can think of none I\'ve enjoyed more.\"\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Bradley Russell, Audience Member (Erie, PA)</b></span>\n<h3></h3>\n\"Delightful young and enthusiastic kids.  They played from their lives, and bounced around the stage and hall.  All nations, all Bach/Irish, all compositions were excellently played.  Folk, Classical.  Wow!\"\n<span style=\"font-size: small;\"><b>-Review by Ratevka on Goldstar (Berkeley, CA)</b></span>','Quotes','','inherit','closed','open','','73-autosave-v1','','','