Ancient Dances</span></h3>\r\nUp-tempo dance tunes and classical works from Ireland, England, Sweden, Denmark, Norway &amp; Germany accompanied by a narrative - theatrically woven throughout the program - that tells the story of where the music traveled and how it came to be.  <a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Ancient-Dances.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Click for more info</span></a>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #8a359c;\">Japan Meets World</span></h3>\r\nAn exploration of Japan\'s most beloved folk songs and anime soundtracks.  Also featured are contemporary chamber works and Maria\'s compositions (for flute, violin, cello, voice &amp; dance) that transform western instruments into a traditional Japanese orchestra.  <a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Japan-Meets-World.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Click for more info</span></a>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #8a359c;\">Echoing Voices: A Musical History of America</span></h3>\r\nMusic from the homelands of immigrants through their stories and history of coming to America.  The music of 10 regions - the Netherlands, England, Ireland, Germany, Russia, Italy, Puerto Rico, Mexico, Egypt and China - is featured alongside interactive activities for audience members of all ages.  (Canadian version of <i>Echoing Voices</i> also available.)  <a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/Echoing-Voices.pdf\" target=\"_blank\"><span>Click for more info</span></a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Sonic-Escape-Echoing-Voices-Study-Guide-US.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download <em>Echoing Voices</em> study guide (US version)</a>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Sonic_Escape-Echoing-Voice-Study-Guide-CAN.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download<em> Echoing Voices</em> study guide (Canadian version)</a>\r\n<h3><span style=\"color: #8a359c;\">Around the World</span></h3>\r\n<span style=\"line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;\">The flute and violin are two of the world\'s most beloved instruments, and their likeness can be found in virtually every culture’s music.  In this program, Shawn and Maria perform a rich blend of classical and world music from Germany, Ireland, Japan, China, the Czech Republic, Norway, Sweden, Denmark, Uruguay, the United States and Canada.  </span><a style=\"line-height: 1.714285714; font-size: 1rem;\" href=\"http://youtu.be/Bcw3BYut0qQ\" target=\"_blank\">Click for video</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Sonic-Escape-Around-the-World-Study-Guide.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Download<em> Around the World</em> study guide</a>','More','','inherit','closed','open','','104-revision-v1','','','2014-03-09 23:17:00','2014-03-09 23:17:00','',104,'http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/104-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(773,1,'2014-03-19 03:37:51','2014-03-19 03:37:51','\"Wonderfully imaginative,\" \"smile-inducing,\" \"impressive\" and \"designed to entertain\" - just some of what Stephen Brookes from the <em>Washington Post</em> had to say about <em>Sonic Escape\'s</em> original works and performance at the Evermay Estate!  <a href=\"http://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/music/sonic-escape-with-folk-classical-music-at-evermay-estate/2014/03/16/93aeeed2-ad19-11e3-b8b3-44b1d1cd4c1f_story.html\" target=\"_blank\">Click here to read the full review!!</a>','Great review in the Washington Post!','','inherit','closed','open','','772-revision-v1','','','2014-03-19 03:37:51','2014-03-19 03:37:51','',772,'http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/772-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(776,1,'2014-03-19 03:48:50','2014-03-19 03:48:50','','Washington Post','','inherit','closed','open','','washington-post','','','2014-03-19 03:48:50','2014-03-19 03:48:50','',0,'http://www.sonicescapemusic.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/Washington-Post.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(778,1,'2014-03-19 03:51:2